obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2229  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Spine changes induced by Stau1 siRNA are prevented by NMDA receptor blockade and high Mg2+\"\nFig.2: \"Impairment of FSK-induced L-LTP after Stau1 knockdown during high Mg2+ treatment\"\n\nTogether: mRNA binding/transporting protein Stau1 regulates spine morphology and late-LTP induction. The role in late-LTP induction is independent of the role in morphological changes. Literal: \"In conclusion, we found that Stau1 involvement in spine morphogenesis is dependent on NMDA receptor-mediated plasticity in hippocampal pyramidal cells. We also found that Stau1 is required for late-LTP, independently of its role in spine morphogenesis\"\n\nNote: the role as mRNA binding/transporting protein is not shown in this paper.. Experimental description: - Slice culture: The species of the cells is not stated in the paper. I have derived the species, rat, from a remark on the specificity of the shRNA sequences: \"siRNA target sequences for rat were as described\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2229" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

